From Ivan D Reid Subject Re Electricty In article , Mr Bill writes Norman Hamer writes NH Trying to figure out a way to put a halogen beam on my CB T Are NH there any easy ways to do this i e a slip in bulb replacement No The Honda s employed a sealed beam which was not interchangeable with anything else, so far as I could ever tell I've owned two s over the years, and that was always one of my biggest nits I'm not sure how far standardisation went, but on two of my bikes the GS B and, I think, the GT M I was able to pop a Cibie' insert directly into the original housing held in by those roughly W shaped springs The inserts used W halogen bulbs, and were great, although Mr Bill later indicates that this may be too much of a drain on your charging system Ivan Reid, Paul Scherrer Institute, CH GSX F, RG WD SI You Porsche Me pass DoD